						               													<description>In Anabid!, players compete to outspell, outbid and outwit their opponents to achieve the highest score.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After the custom 6- and 8-sided lettered dice are rolled, the first player states a word length and bids how many words that long they think they can spell.  Each subsequent bid must increase the number of words or the word length.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player has a scant few seconds to make a bid and each bid is an opportunity to drive the next player to unwisely overbid -- a core strategy.  The top bidder has a minute to fulfil his bid.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Words with greater lengths garner higher scores.  To counter Aunt Edna's dictionary memorization, however, the game includes a clever mechanism that enables a would-be thief to steal the bid score!  After each player has rolled three times (with the middle round in reverse order), the player with the highest score wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
